---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="FAQ" description="Find answers to frequently asked questions about Codex Helper, including setup instructions, subscription details, and how to get support.">
    <script type="application/ld+json" slot="head-scripts">
    {
        "@context": "https://schema.org",
        "@type": "FAQPage",
        "mainEntity": [
            {
                "@type": "Question",
                "name": "How do I setup the bot on my discord server?",
                "acceptedAnswer": {
                    "@type": "Answer",
                    "text": "Subscribe to our Patreon page, follow the invite link, link your Discord to Patreon, then run /patreon verify in your server. Use /help for a list of commands."
                }
            },
            {
                "@type": "Question",
                "name": "Do the higher membership tiers of the Patreon page unlock other features?",
                "acceptedAnswer": {
                    "@type": "Answer",
                    "text": "No, the only tier required to use the bot is the lowest tier ($3 USD/month). Higher tiers are for extra support to The King's Codex."
                }
            },
            {
                "@type": "Question",
                "name": "Can I activate the Codex Helper bot in multiple servers after subscribing?",
                "acceptedAnswer": {
                    "@type": "Answer",
                    "text": "Yes, the subscription is tied per person. As long as you are an Administrator or have Manage Server permissions, you can freely add the bot to multiple servers."
                }
            },
            {
                "@type": "Question",
                "name": "I'm having issues with the Codex Helper bot, where can I find support?",
                "acceptedAnswer": {
                    "@type": "Answer",
                    "text": "You can open a ticket in the King's Codex Discord Server in the discord.support channel, or leave feedback in the feedback channel."
                }
            }
        ]
    }
    </script>

    <main class="faq-page-wrapper">
        <section class="faq-hero">
            <div class="faq-hero-container">
                <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
                <p>Find answers to common questions about Codex Helper and get the help you need.</p>
            </div>
        </section>
    
        <section class="faq-content">
            <div class="faq-container">
                <div class="faq-grid">
                    <div class="faq-items">
                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <button class="faq-question">
                                <span>How do I setup the bot on my discord server?</span>
                                <svg class="faq-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
                                    <path d="M6 9L12 15L18 9" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                                </svg>
                            </button>
                            <div class="faq-answer">
                                <p><strong>1.</strong> Subscribe to our Patreon page, then follow the link in the pinned post to invite the Codex Helper bot to your server of choice.</p>
                                <p><strong>2.</strong> Link your Discord account to your Patreon account through the link sent to your Discord DM's by the bot, or here: <br/><a href="https://www.patreon.com/settings/apps" target="_blank">https://www.patreon.com/settings/apps</a></p>
                                <p><strong>3.</strong> Run the <code>/patreon verify</code> command in any channel of the server you invited the Codex Helper bot to.</p>
                                <p><strong>4.</strong> Use <code>/help</code> for a list of commands, especially <code>/channel</code> or other <code>/(feature) setup</code> commands to get started.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <button class="faq-question">
                                <span>Do the higher membership tiers of the Patreon page unlock other features?</span>
                                <svg class="faq-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
                                    <path d="M6 9L12 15L18 9" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                                </svg>
                            </button>
                            <div class="faq-answer">
                                <p>No, the only tier required to use the bot is the lowest tier ($3 USD/month). The higher tiers are simply for extra support to The King's Codex.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <button class="faq-question">
                                <span>Can I activate the Codex Helper bot in multiple servers after subscribing?</span>
                                <svg class="faq-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
                                    <path d="M6 9L12 15L18 9" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                                </svg>
                            </button>
                            <div class="faq-answer">
                                <p>Yes, the subscription is tied per person therefore as long as you are an Administrator or have Manage Server permissions within a discord server, you can freely add the bot.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <button class="faq-question">
                                <span>I'm having issues with the Codex Helper bot, where can I find support?</span>
                                <svg class="faq-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
                                    <path d="M6 9L12 15L18 9" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                                </svg>
                            </button>
                            <div class="faq-answer">
                                <p>You can open a ticket in the King's Codex Discord Server, specifically in the <strong>discordâ€¤support</strong> channel found here: <br/><a href="https://discord.com/channels/1031515159627300924/1314193270078967829" target="_blank">https://discord.com/channels/1031515159627300924/1314193270078967829</a><br/>Open a "Codex Helper" ticket and Ruz will respond when available.</p>
                                <p>Likewise you can also leave feedback about the bot in the <strong>feedback</strong> channel found here: <br/><a href="https://discord.com/channels/1031515159627300924/1320650068751155200" target="_blank">https://discord.com/channels/1031515159627300924/1320650068751155200</a></p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
    
                <div class="faq-contact">
                    <div class="contact-card">
                        <h3>Still need help?</h3>
                        <p>Can't find the answer you're looking for? Join The King's Codex Discord server for support.</p>
                        <div class="contact-buttons">
                            <a href="https://discord.com/channels/1031515159627300924/1314193270078967829" target="_blank" class="btn-primary"><i class="fa-brands fa-discord"></i> Join Support Server</a>
                            <a href="https://discord.com/channels/1031515159627300924/1320650068751155200" target="_blank" class="btn-secondary">Leave Feedback</a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>
</Layout>